This has certainly changed the understanding of culture lead by connecting people across the world instantly on one giant virtual platform in which we all communicate, learn from and take part in. The main impact on PNG culture... Is the influence of foreign products, services and ideas that are distributed and adopted without the origin of their concept in consideration. Emerging with this influence of globalization is the understanding that sustainable practice in the development of a community is outside of the philosophical concept of wealth in Western culture.

Paradoxically, this is the nucleus which lies behind the definition and meaning of culture to its people. Culture is not just some individual who is well dressed, smart and articulate but a life style that is intertwined with renewable land, social awareness and habitat protection in which we operate from and inculcates. Papua New Guinea must determine and resolve clearly how this balance and relationship of its recent past and newer contemporary view shall work in the next 20 years; instantly southwestern cultures were forced to adapt and accepted the historical and modern China or Russia or African cultures but will be forced to accept the western culture at the expense of the environment. In my respectful opinion, Britain must accept that development needs to take account for Papua New Guinea in which prosperity be measured in the context of social integrity in the future and this would be monitored by a world look against the measurement of the environment.
